  <p>
    If you have simple, routine questions: We have condensed our 40+ years of disc-stack centrifuge experience into <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge-faq/">101 Frequently Asked Questions about Disc Stack Centrifuges</a>.
  </p>

  <h2 id="mopx-310">Also Available: MOPX 310 Total-Discharge</h2>

  <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start not-prose mb-6">
    <div class="md:w-1/2">
      <p class="text-text-light mb-4">
        The Alfa Laval MOPX 310 is a self-cleaning disc-stack centrifuge in the same size class, designed for three-phase separation of <a href="/centrifuge-pyrolysis-oil/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">industrial oil</a>, <a href="/lube-oil-centrifuge/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">lube oil</a>, <a href="/wvo-centrifuge-separator/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">WVO</a>, <a href="/black-diesel-centrifuge/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">black diesel</a>, and other mineral oils. With a 10 HP motor at 5,180 RPM, it processes 25 GPM of used oil at 180&deg;F.
      </p>
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <tbody>
          <tr class="bg-white border-b border-gray-200">
            <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold text-navy">Model Type</td>
